Money Stuff =0A Two approximately true things about the US stock market are=
: Companies are =0Arequired to publicly disclose everything about themselve=
s that mi =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=3D825881=
&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D12072878&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525&p=3D1218=
2024>=0A=0A=0A=0APisces=0A=0ATwo approximately true things about the US sto=
ck market are:=0A=0A * Companies are required to publicly disclose everythi=
ng about themselves =0Athat might be material to investors. This isn=E2=80=
=99t exactly true, [1]  <> and it =0Adoesn=E2=80=99t work seamlessly: Compa=
nies generally announce quarterly earnings =0Ashortly after the quarter end=
s, but there=E2=80=99s some period of time when the =0Acompany=E2=80=99s ex=
ecutives pretty much know what the earnings release will say, but =0Ait has=
n=E2=80=99t been published yet. Or companies will often negotiate mergers w=
ithout =0Afirst announcing =E2=80=9Chey we=E2=80=99re in merger talks,=E2=
=80=9D which is something that investors =0Awould probably want to know. Bu=
t for the most part investors expect that most =0Amaterial information abou=
